{Filtration}
Filtration is carried out by 16 rapid gravity filters. The actual filtering material is one metre of graded sand and anthracite. The design filtration rate is 87m/m2/d but rates of 130/m2/d are regularly obtained.
To aid the filtration process, a small amount of coagulant, aluminium sulphate, is added to the water prior to the filters. This coagulant combines with the soluble organic matter to form a microfloc. This microfloc is retained in the filter as an insoluble precipitate and hence improves the quality of the filtered water.
